==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rehearsal
<hw>Re*hears"al</hw> <pr>(r?*h?rs"<it>a</it>)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>The act of rehearsing; recital; narration; repetition;
specifically, a private recital, performance, or season of practice, in
preparation for a public exhibition or exercise.</def>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In <qex>rehearsal</qex> of our Lord's Prayer.</q>
<rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Here's marvelous convenient place for our
<qex>rehearsal</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Dress rehearsal</b></col> <fld>(Theater)</fld>, <cd>a
private preparatory performance of a drama, opera, etc., in
costume.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rehearse</ent>⟦br⟧
